child's education is the most important contribution you make in their lives but it does not just stop there. Being involved on a daily basis and knowing what your child is being taught and reinforce homework and participate with their daily assignments to insure they comprehend what is being taught. Allowing a child to participate at their own pace is a sure road to failure. Set standards and goals for your child at an early age and they will get a good education. Book learning trumps soccer, little league, and all other extra curricular activities. Providing a private education for your child is exactly the point at hand. Your child's education is YOUR responsibility....public and private education provide the opportunities but it up to you as parents to insure that you and your child take full advantage of these opportunities. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1149" language="en" documentId="3797" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="john almasi (1REDVETTE)" date="Aug 29, 2013 6:33PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="4" thumbsDown="0" origId="3797" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1149"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>